    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="400"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Emperor</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">McKinley</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamburg Schloss</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I received with pleasure the decision of the United States that American and
                    German soldiers shall fight together for the common cause of civilization under
                    one commander in chief. The brave army of your country which have shown of late
                    so many warlike qualities, united with Europe, will be irresistible. Field
                    Marshal Count Waldersee, who will have the honor of leading your forces, is not
                    a stranger to America. His wife is an American by birth. I beg your excellency
                    to accept my heartfelt thanks for the confidence the United States place in the
                    leadership of Count Waldersee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilhelm II.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
